<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-02-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">761.13/2–2650: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Barbour</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-02-26">February 26,
                                1950</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>676. Soviet Press February 26 carries decree Supreme Soviet USSR ordering
                            separation naval forces from Ministry Armed Forces and formation
                            All-Union Naval Ministry USSR. Ministry Armed Forces renamed War
                            Ministry. Admiral I. S. Yumashev named Naval Minister.<note n="1" xml:id="d609fn1">Admiral Ivan Stepanovich Yumashev was the Commander
                                in Chief of the Naval Forces of the Soviet Union, 1947–1951.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Barbour</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>